Question: Many universities require that freshman live on campus dorm during the first year of college. In your opinion, is this a good or a bad thing? Explain your opinion on this issue.
Answer:
It is a good thing because it encourages many students to interact early on, who would otherwise be cut off from new contacts.  By year two, if they haven't made any friends it's probably too late.  Some people have legitimate concerns about price, so they should make housing cheaper for freshmen since the dorms usually suck.